  "prompt": "What is Akand Sitra's daily schedule while preparing for his UPSC exams?",
  "response": "Akand Sitra's daily schedule while preparing for his UPSC exams is highly structured and disciplined. Here's a detailed breakdown of his typical day:\n\n**5:00 AM - Wake Up and Morning Routine**\n- Akand wakes up early at 5:00 AM to kickstart his day.\n- He spends the first 30 minutes on personal hygiene and getting ready.\n\n**5:30 AM - 6:30 AM - Physical Exercise**\n- He dedicates an hour to physical fitness, often engaging in jogging or yoga to keep his mind and body in optimal condition.\n\n**6:30 AM - 7:00 AM - Meditation and Breakfast**\n- After exercising, Akand spends 30 minutes meditating to clear his mind and set his intentions for the day.\n- He then has a light, nutritious breakfast.\n\n**7:00 AM - 9:00 AM - Current Affairs and Newspaper Reading**\n- Akand spends two hours going through newspapers and current affairs materials to stay updated on national and international events.\n\n**9:00 AM - 12:00 PM - Core Subject Study**\n- He allocates three hours to studying core subjects like History, Geography, or Polity, depending on his study plan for the week.\n\n**12:00 PM - 1:00 PM - Lunch and Short Break**\n- Akand takes a one-hour break for lunch, often using this time to relax or listen to music.\n\n**1:00 PM - 3:00 PM - Optional Subject Study**\n- He spends two hours studying his optional subject, which requires in-depth knowledge and understanding.\n\n**3:00 PM - 4:00 PM - Revision and Note-making**\n- Akand uses this hour to revise what he has studied during the day and make notes for quick reference.\n\n**4:00 PM - 5:00 PM - Break and Refreshment**\n- He takes another break to refresh his mind, often engaging in light activities or socializing with family.\n\n**5:00 PM - 7:00 PM - Practice Tests and Question Papers**\n- Akand dedicates two hours to solving practice tests and previous years' question papers to gauge his preparation level.\n\n**7:00 PM - 8:00 PM - Dinner and Family Time**\n- He has dinner with his family, using this time to unwind and discuss non-academic topics.\n\n**8:00 PM - 10:00 PM - Additional Study or Weak Areas**\n- Akand spends two more hours focusing on any weak areas or additional topics that need attention.\n\n**10:00 PM - 10:30 PM - Evening Routine and Relaxation**\n- He winds down with a light evening routine, which might include reading fiction or watching educational videos.\n\n**10:30 PM - 11:00 PM - Planning for the Next Day**\n- Akand spends 30 minutes planning his schedule for the next day, ensuring he stays on track with his study plan.\n\n**11:00 PM - Bedtime**\n- He goes to bed by 11:00 PM to ensure he gets enough sleep for another productive day.\n\nThis rigorous schedule showcases Akand Sitra's dedication and strategic approach to preparing for the UPSC exams, balancing intense study sessions with necessary breaks and personal time.",
